<TITLE> ACC sues Khaleda for corruption links </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Sept 2 (bdnews24.com)  The Anticorruption Commission Sunday night sued Khaleda Zia and her son Arafat Rahman Coco for their links to corruption. A deputy director of the ACC, Golam Shahriar Chowdhury, filed the case against 13 people, including the two, with Tejgaon Police Station. The former prime minister is accused of appointing Global Agro Trade Company (GATCO) as a contractor for both the Inland Container Depot in Kamalapur and the Chittagong port on March 1, 2003 without following a proper bidding procedure. GATCO, a private handling company, is often blamed for inefficiency in handling containers. The shady recruitment of GATCO and subsequent problems arising from it cost the state coffers Tk 1,000 crore, according to case details. Khaleda is facing allegations of abusing power as prime minister. The case was filed at 11:15pm. Following are the 13 people listed in the case: Khaleda Zia Retired Commodore Julfiker Ali, former chairman of Chittagong Port Authority (CPA) AM Shahdat Hossain, former chairman of CPA AM Sanwar Hossain, former director of CPA Ahmed Abul Kashem, chief accounts officer of CPA Lutful Kabir, former member of CPA Ismail Hossain Saimon, son of the late shipping minister Akbar Hossain Arafat Rahman Coco, son of Khaleda Syed Galib Ahmed, director of Global Agro Trade Private Limited Company Syed Tanvir Ahmed, director of Global Agro Trade AKM Musa Kazal, director of Global Agro Trade Jahanara Ansar, resident of new DOHS Ehsan Yusuf, director of Global Agro Trade bdnews
